87_2020.doc&d=nCDZGLdcAmB0c2Oxl6asXA2E5jpmEl9YQHmcT4noKO0%3D&h=e8a13ddf\" target=\"_blank\">https://legalref.judiciary.hk/doc/judg/word/vetted/other/en/2020/HCAL001087_2020.doc</a><br />\n<br />\n百鳩幾頁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-03T09:25:55.000Z","msg":"大體係話證據上顯示考評局嘅專業人士有考慮到唔同因素，而且無明顯證據顯示政府有迫啲成員做某啲決定，所以就唔推翻了<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/math.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n[271]<br />\nI am afraid I do think that some of the public statements made by the EDB and/or the Secretary for Education were conveyed &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"color: red;\">in a most high-profile and threatening manner</span></strong>&rdquo;, just as Ms Po submits.  But those statements were made publicly outside the deliberations of the HKEAA Council, and I do not think the evidence demonstrates that they created improper pressure on Council members, or forced Council members somehow to jettison their own independent thoughts and decisions.  As Mr Suen submits, the <strong><span style=\"color: red;\">HKEAA Council members are educated individuals and should be able to make their own independent decision</span></strong>, taking into account relevant factors and giving them such weight as they think appropriate.  Again, I do not think it would be fair to infer from the strength of opinion, or forcefulness in presentation, anything which would render the decision-making process unlawful."},{"pid":"8df142238a202252b1493fd80c645d3136487d34","tid":2092038,"uid":84415,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"91760a9ba1413037c372413d9656c52c867101d5","tid":2092038,"uid":7542,"like":0,"dislike":8,"score":-8,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-07-03T09:00:02.000Z","msg":"Update: 學生敗訴<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/eQSiq9D.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FeQSiq9D.png&h=a2f3c70f&s={SIZE}\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-03T09:36:12.000Z","msg